# Common Lisp Style

- Use `package-inferred-system`: each file starts with `defpackage`, one package per file.
- Declare dependencies via `:import-from` in `defpackage` (not `:use` except for `:cl`).
- Use `alexandria:define-constant` with `:test #'equal` for string constants (SBCL compat).
- Use `alexandria:when-let` instead of custom macros.
- JSON: `yason:parse` to decode, `(with-output-to-string (s) (yason:encode obj s))` to encode.
- Constructors: `make-<class>` keyword functions (not raw `make-instance`).
- Conditions: define with `define-condition`, signal with `error`/`signal`.
- Exports: list in `defpackage :export`, aggregate in `all.lisp` via `uiop:define-package :use-reexport`.
- Register external packages in `.asd`: `(register-system-packages "lib" '(:lib))`.
- Line length: 120 chars max.
